                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18230514-120-off640 t18230514-120-crimeloc643"></join>. I missed a pair of chaise wings about the end of April, and found them at Bateman's. The prisoner worked for me towards the end of February.</p>
               <p>HORACE BATEMAN. I live in Eagle-street, Red Lion-square. The prisoner came several times for work, which his master did for me, and on Good Friday he offered these wings for sale - I gave him 4 s. for them. He said he had taken them out as wages.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
